E, the two halfe bastions D and F, and the tenaile DC, &amp; hauing drawn the lines round about the town, lea|uing sufficient space be<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">wene them and the walls to build bulwarkes or bastions, you may take for the length of euery line of defence, that is to say from the flanke of one bastion to the point of another, 100. or 110 fa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">hom and so euery bastion shall bee scow|red with musket-shot, as the forts built regularly. This may serue for an example to those who by chance, may haue occasio~ to repair or streng|then any part of a towne, wall, or the whole, and for the fortifying of the wall, the earth must be raised in the inside as a rampard.</P>
