<HEAD>CHAP. X. Multiplication of Fractions.</HEAD>
<P>LEt there bee proposed a superfi|cies in the forme of a paralello|gram, vulgarly cald square, the sides whereof the one is in length 7/8 of a fa|thom, and the other in breadth &frac34;, and these two fractions are to bee multi|plied together to find out how much the whole superficies doth containe the figures must be disposed as follo|weth.
