<HEAD>CHAP. XI. Multiplication of entiers and Fractions.</HEAD>
<P>TO multiply &frac14; by 2&frac12;, you must first of al reduce the whole into fracti|ons, and then as here aboue multi|ply numerator by numerator, and de|nominator by denominator, and the product will bee 45/<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">8, as plainely ap|peares by the example following.
