<DIV2 N="14" TYPE="chapter">
<PB N="245" REF="132">
<HEAD>CHAP. XIV. Evaluation of fractions which may not be abridged.</HEAD>
<P>SVppose you were to abridge 7/9 parts of a fathom, first you must consider what are the parts of the intier or whole, as 6. foot, or 72. inches: then you must multiply the numerator 7, by the denominator 72 parts, and let the product bee di|uided by the denominator 9, and then you will finde 56 inches for the eualuation of 7/9 parts of a fathom.
<PB N="246" REF="133">
